==English==

===Etymology===
{{wikipedia}}
Originally an African American form of [[music]] and [[dance]], in which [[cake]] was offered as a prize for the best dancers.

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-cakewalk.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''cakewalk'''
# A contest in which cake was offered for the best dancers
# {{music}} The style of music associated with such a contest.
# The dance, or style of dance associated with such a contest.
# Something that is [[easy]] or [[simple]], or does not present any great [[challenge]].
#:''I've known this material for a long time, so the test on it should be a '''cakewalk'''.''
{{seeCites}}

